kpa.model

Class KEntry

  • java.lang.Object
    • kpa.model.AbstractGroup
      • kpa.model.KEntry
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Iterable<KCell>

    public class KEntry
extends AbstractGroup
    Entry in a Kakuro puzzle, consisting of a location, direction, a specification, and a group of cells. The location, direction, and specification are immutable. The group of cells is mutable, and set cell-by-cell during construction. An entry traverses two phases:
    1. Constructor sets location, direction, and specification.
    2. During puzzle set-up, cells are associated.
    3. During solving, all cells have been associated (see invariant Size), and should not change any more.
    Invariant:
    NoBlocked: (\forall cell : this; ! cell.isBlocked),
    Size: this.getCount() == this.specification.getLength()
